<p class="page" id="a3671161">[Page 161]</p>
<p>This coast of Arabia is very desolute &amp; dismal. Not a light or marks to be seen for over a thousand miles on its coast. The tribes there being semecivilized &amp; hostile by nature, yet as luck happens they bear the Turk such animosity that now thousands of them are fighting against the Turks &amp; therefore helping the Allies. King Hessian a Arab King is doing good work with his thousands of troops, carrying out a raiding fight &amp; helping the Allies immensely.<br/>This country was formally ruled by the Suntan of Turkey, the method of government barbarous. Now these Arab troops have advanced from Mesepotamia to the North of Palastine.<br/>Practically all the potatoes we took aboard as stores at Suez for the Indian troops have gone bad in the course of the 1st 4 days out. The excessive heat during the 1st few days. These potatoes cost &pound;65 per ton at Suez, potatoes there being exceedingly scarce &amp; dear.</p>
